OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F362A1774455106
OL,3,C'Terrible' or 'brave'? Rally
OL,4,Chighlights divisions over Farage
OL,6,FIf you needed any more evidence of how
OL,7,Fdivisive a figure Nigel Farage is, you
OL,8,Fwould have found it at the Leeds Arena
OL,9,Fon Tuesday night.
OL,11,FReform had booked the venue, which can
OL,12,Fhold more than 13,000 people, for
OL,13,Ftheir first rally in the region as
OL,14,Fcampaigning ramps up ahead of the
OL,15,Flocal elections in May.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G1/12
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,363,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36202
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F362A1774455106
OL,3,C'Terrible' or 'brave'? Rally
OL,4,Chighlights divisions over Farage
OL,6,FBefore people started filing in, I had
OL,7,Fa chance conversation with a couple of
OL,8,Ffriends, who weren't attending the
OL,9,Fevent. Their difference of opinion on
OL,10,FFarage crystallised the two sides of
OL,11,Fthe debate.
OL,13,F"I think he's terrible," said one. "I
OL,14,Fhate him."
OL,16,F"I think he's very brave and very
OL,17,Fintelligent," said the other.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G2/12
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,363,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F362A1774455106
OL,3,C'Terrible' or 'brave'? Rally
OL,4,Chighlights divisions over Farage
OL,6,FThere was obvious surprise from both
OL,7,Fat how the conversation had
OL,8,Ftemporarily upset their pleasant
OL,9,Fafternoon out - and a reminder that
OL,10,Fthe Reform leader provokes many
OL,11,Freactions, but rarely apathy.
OL,13,FThere were further reminders
OL,14,Fimmediately outside the arena.
OL,16,FAs the party faithful arrived in the
OL,17,Fpouring rain, many decked in the
OL,18,Fturquoise colours of Reform, they were
OL,19,Fgreeted by a crowd of protestors.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G3/12
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,363,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F362A1774455106
OL,3,C'Terrible' or 'brave'? Rally
OL,4,Chighlights divisions over Farage
OL,6,FThe former group sees him as a
OL,7,Fpolitical superstar, the fix for a
OL,8,Fcountry they think is broken.
OL,10,FThe latter see him as a divider, a man
OL,11,Fwho uses the politics of exclusion to
OL,12,Fwin votes.
OL,14,FAs both groups waited for the rally to
OL,15,Fstart, the two opposing visions of
OL,16,FNigel Farage came, quite literally,
OL,17,Fface to face.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G4/12
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,363,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36205
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F362A1774455106
OL,3,C'Terrible' or 'brave'? Rally
OL,4,Chighlights divisions over Farage
OL,6,FInside the arena, the crowd may not
OL,7,Fhave matched the potential capacity -
OL,8,Fjust over 1,000 were due to attend -
OL,9,Fbut Reform still put on a now well-
OL,10,Frehearsed show.
OL,12,FWith audience participation, highly
OL,13,Fproduced videos, and dramatic music
OL,14,Fand lighting, it was more reminiscent
OL,15,Fof the music and comedy gigs that the
OL,16,Farena normally hosts.
OL,18,FBut the performance had a clear
OL,19,Fpolitical message.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G5/12
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,363,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36206
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F362A1774455106
OL,3,C'Terrible' or 'brave'? Rally
OL,4,Chighlights divisions over Farage
OL,6,FGreater Lincolnshire Mayor Andrea
OL,7,FJenkyns welcomed the crowd to what she
OL,8,Fdescribed as "bonkers Britain" and
OL,9,Fattacked 'Net Zero' saying the region
OL,10,Fneeded fracking.
OL,12,FAshfield MP Lee Anderson followed her
OL,13,Fsaying that Islamophobia is a "made up
OL,14,Fword by Labour politicians to help
OL,15,Fsave their safe city seats".
OL,17,FAnd then came the man the crowd had
OL,18,Fbeen waiting for: Nigel Farage.
OL,20,F"We love you, Nigel," one person
OL,21,Fshouted. "Go on, Nigel," said another.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G6/12
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,363,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36207
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F362A1774455106
OL,3,C'Terrible' or 'brave'? Rally
OL,4,Chighlights divisions over Farage
OL,6,FFarage hit his usual talking points -
OL,7,Fleaving the European Convention on
OL,8,FHuman Rights, attacking small boat
OL,9,Fcrossings - and ended with a signal of
OL,10,Fhis ambitions in the region.
OL,12,F"I believe we have every chance of
OL,13,Fwinning in Barnsley, in South
OL,14,FYorkshire, in Wakefield just down the
OL,15,Froad," he said, before asking Reform
OL,16,Fcandidates in those areas to join him
OL,17,Fon stage.
OL,19,FBut what would Reform actually do if
OL,20,Fit matches that prediction?
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G7/12
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,363,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36208
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F362A1774455106
OL,3,C'Terrible' or 'brave'? Rally
OL,4,Chighlights divisions over Farage
OL,6,FEarlier in the day I met Nigel Farage
OL,7,Fin a pub in Churwell where he stopped
OL,8,Ffor a pint before the rally.
OL,10,FI asked whether residents in those
OL,11,Fcouncils would see their taxes
OL,12,Fdecrease.
OL,14,F"Yes," came the reply as he referenced
OL,15,Fto the "hundreds of millions of
OL,16,Fpounds" Reform says it has saved in
OL,17,Fthe councils it already runs.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G8/12
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,363,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36209
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F362A1774455106
OL,3,C'Terrible' or 'brave'? Rally
OL,4,Chighlights divisions over Farage
OL,6,FI pointed out that, in our region,
OL,7,FReform-run Derbyshire County Council
OL,8,Fwill increase council tax by 4.9% and
OL,9,FLincolnshire County Council is raising
OL,10,Fit by 2.9%.
OL,12,F"I've never once promised we'd cut
OL,13,Fcouncil tax" he said. "Never once in
OL,14,Fthe campaign last year did I promise
OL,15,FI'd cut council tax and nor am I
OL,16,Fpromising it this year."
OL,18,FSo Reform isn't pledging to cut your
OL,19,Fcouncil tax bills.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G9/12
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,363,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36210
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F362A1774455106
OL,3,C'Terrible' or 'brave'? Rally
OL,4,Chighlights divisions over Farage
OL,6,FWhat about transport investment in the
OL,7,Fregion through Northern Powerhouse
OL,8,FRail, given that Reform has been
OL,9,Fsceptical of the plan in the past?
OL,11,F"A Farage government does not waste
OL,12,Ftens of billions of pounds on projects
OL,13,Fthat will be delivered late...we can
OL,14,Fdo it far better," he tells me.
OL,16,FFarage and Reform still top the polls,
OL,17,Fbut the party's challenge is turning
OL,18,Fthat support into seats.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1        G10/12
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,363,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36211
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F362A1774455106
OL,3,C'Terrible' or 'brave'? Rally
OL,4,Chighlights divisions over Farage
OL,6,FAlready some are seeing a trend among
OL,7,Fthe electorate they have titled 'ABR'
OL,8,F- Anyone But Reform - meaning voters
OL,9,Ftactically cast their ballot to avoid
OL,10,FFarage's party winning power.
OL,12,FThere are many voters who will walk
OL,13,Finto polling stations on election day
OL,14,Fin May proudly supporting Reform, and
OL,15,Fthere are many others who will vote
OL,16,Fspecifically to oppose them.
OL,18,FThe final balance between those views
OL,19,Fwill decide how successful the party
OL,20,Fis in the region.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1        G11/12
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
